er time I have seen people mention that there must be something more than this physical world and universe, otherwise there is no purpose.  I tend to think that things happen without necessarily having a purpose.  Do all strong believers think we are here for a particular purpose?  Even if there is life after death, what would the purpose of that be?  What is the purpose of just sitting up there on a cloud or just merely existing day in and day out for all eternity?  Also, what about the purpose of particular life events?  Is there really a purpose to a baby being left to overheat in a locked car or a purpose to a young teenager dying in an accident (yes, the latter is a little personal to me)?  I am happy living my life for the here and now, but so many others are just focused on some bigger picture that nobody can truly grasp.  Some people think that you can't find joy in life without finding joy in an afterlife.  To me this is like turning down an invitation to a party just because there won't be another party the next day.  We go to a party in order to enjoy that given moment, and we have fun at these parties eventhough we know it will end.  When I showed up at my wedding I looked forward to the next 6 hours of fun.  I didn't sit there and say &quot;what is the point of being here if it is just going to end?&quot;.  Some thoughts...<br>
<br>
Stacey <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dagrom>dagrom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#3333ff>(2/17/03 9:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.growthspurts.com/drivee/images/515993215336.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Purpose In Life</span><hr size=1> i actually think there is some common ground here...<br>
<br>
we are all here that we might have joy.<br>
