i'm just glad that most spirits are true to the self evident truths of life, liberty, and the pursuit of happiness (where ever one chooses to pursue that happiness) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#9fb7df><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ians1mom>ians1mom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#3333ff>(2/18/03 1:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Purpose In Life</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>To me this is like turning down an invitation to a party just because there won't be another party the next day. We go to a party in order to enjoy that given moment, and we have fun at these parties eventhough we know it will end.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Actually, I am quite enjoying this present party AND I know I get to go to another one once this one ends. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Just because I believe in Heaven and that I will be there one day does not in any way diminish my joy at this life. I cannot tell you how many times each day I sit back, stare at my son, and think, &quot;Wow, he's something else!&quot; (And I mean this, usually, in a good way!) Seriously, though, this life is meant to be enjoyed. It is my belief that God created us to love Him, love each other, and be loved by others. My life is about trying to experience that. My purpose right now in this present life is to be the best daughter, wife, mother, teacher, sister, aunt, etc., that I can be. Most the time, it is a very fulfilling experience. Granted, there are really low and bummer times. My m/c made me really wonder why some things are allowed. It took a long time to come up out of that pit. But, eventually the fog began to clear and the goodness of life came back. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What is the purpose of just sitting up there on a cloud or just merely existing day in and day out for all eternity?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
You know, I have such a hard time even conceptualizing Heaven. I don't think, though, that it will be merely existing day in and day out. First of all, I do not believe that our concept of time will exist. But sometimes I still wonder, &quot;Will I get bored?&quot; But then I think about being in church, singing away with our praise band; or I think about being at a Christian concert, blending my voice with the 1000's of others there, and think, I could do this forever. That's what I think it will be like. Those who make it will all be there for the same purpose - to sing praises to God for eternity. No tears, no sorrow, no pain, no hunger, no needs. So, from a Christian standpoint, the purpose of being there is to lend voice (and hopefully our voices get perfected, because I don't know if God would want to listen to mine for that long! LOL) in praise of Him. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Also, what about the purpose of particular life events?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I'm not sure if there is always an answer for this. I went through this off and on after my m/c. I wanted to know that if God knew I would m/c, why did I become pregnant in the first place. I also went through this when my nephew died. But, I can also see good that has come out of it. BUT, this has taken much time and distance to focus on. I really didn't like people telling me in the moments that everything had its reason and God had a purpose. Yes, I knew deep down this was true, but it didn't make the hurt and pain go away. Now, I see my niece who is an amazing girl and probably came because of the death of her brother. I see the drastic changes in my life - quit one job in the middle of a school year and began another - that probably wouldn't have happened without something as devastating as my m/c. So, ultimately, I do see a purpose for events happening, though I don't think we are always privy to that information. <br>
<br>
I don't believe, though, that God chooses for &quot;bad&quot; things to happen. This would involved a whole 'nother conversation about Adam, sin, free choice, etc. I do believe He allows things to happen, but we choose our own paths in our lives. It is up to us if we are willing to bend our choices to His will or if we are going to go it alone. But no where in the Bible does it say that once you believe in God or choose to follow Him will your life be easy. Nor does it point out that your life will be any worse for the wear if you don't follow Him. (I know there are some out there that are probably chomping at the bit to bring up Scripture to the opposite, but I believe the original post was written in sincerity and I am replying in the same way.) Just look at Paul's life for an example of the &quot;easy&quot; life after following Christ. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
Anyways, you brought up some very interesting points about life. I hope I have given you a little insight possibly into one way at looking at it.<br>
<br>
Brit <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dagrom>dagrom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#3333ff>(2/18/03 9:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=118.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.growthspurts.com/drivee/images/515993215336.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Purpose In Life</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Those who make it will all be there for the same purpose - to sing praises to God for eternity<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
