As I do not buy into LDS belief on heaven and &quot;eternal progression,&quot; this comment does not even affect me. I do not believe in levels of glory nor levels in heaven. You either go or you don't. So I'm not terribly worried about whether or not atheists are in a place of eternal progression. My beliefs are that there is one place and one Name by which you get there. <br>
<br>
I do think it preposterous to assume that we will be on the same level as God one day - nor is this my purpose in life. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>if you are truly as happy as you could be singing hymns of praises for all eternity then you should also be happy for others who receive the glory that their spirits obtain.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
